Mozilla caught heat after its new CEO talked about evolving Firefox into a “modern AI browser,” even though Firefox has had optional AI features for a while. Linus and Luke discuss why people reacted like it’s brand new, why market share matters, and why “ban it” is a fantasy when the tech is already everywhere.
